{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place Gruyère cheese in mixing bowl and grate <b>6 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place onions, olive oil, butter, salt, black pepper in mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>, then, sauté <b>10 min\/120°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Scrape bottom of mixing bowl with spatula to loosen caramelised onions.","Sauté a further <b>10-15 min\/120°C\/\/speed <b>. Scrape bottom of mixing bowl with spatula to loosen caramelised onions","Add flour, water and stock cube, mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 3<b>, then cook <b>20 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Adjust seasoning to taste.","Preheat oven grill to 210°C.","Pour soup into heat-proof soup bowls, place 2 baguette slices on top of each bowl and sprinkle with reserved grated Gruyère cheese. Place bowls under the grill until cheese is melted and slightly brown. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g Gruyère cheese, cut in pieces","500 g onions, cut in halves","30 g olive oil","20 g butter","½ tsp salt, plus extra to taste","2 pinches ground black pepper, plus extra to taste","2 tsp plain flour (10 g)","900 g water","1 stock cube (for 0.5 l), chicken or beef","12 slices baguette, slightly stale, or other crusty bread"]}],"id":"r178847","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-Ilq8sQadY1Q\/XZMyvU-xyAI\/AAAAAAAAao0\/iOGZqlJpTBUbnd2MTC-B9JXEyg657gubgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LYufaBVkmfZgDugv.png","title":"Onion soup","publishedAt":"2018-04-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10 g","fat":"13 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"29 g","calories":"1255 kJ \/ 300 kcal"},"usefulItems":"soup bowls, grill","hintsAndTricks":["In <b>step 2,<b> the onions can be sautéed up to <b>15 minutes<b> to increase caramelisation. Brown residue may stick to the bottom of the mixing bowl. Scraping as indicated at the end of steps 2 and 3 will allow the residue to dissolve in step 4."],"basicInfo":["medium","10m","1h","6 portions"]}